goals.question: What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of life expectancy vs fertility rate
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between life expectancy and fertility rate. It can also help us identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different countries?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of population by country
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the population distribution across different countries and identify any countries with significantly higher or lower populations.

goals.question: How has life expectancy changed over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of life expectancy over time
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the trend of life expectancy over time and identify any significant changes or patterns.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rate across different countries?
goals.visualization: Histogram of fertility rate by country
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the distribution of fertility rate across different countries and identify any countries with significantly higher or lower fertility rates.

goals.question: How does population vary across different clusters?
goals.visualization: Box plot of population by cluster
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the variation of population across different clusters and identify any clusters with significantly higher or lower populations.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    pop_by_country = data.groupby('country')['pop'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    pop_by_country.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different countries?')
    plt.legend(['Population'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('How has life expectancy changed over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['fertility'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['fertility'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across different countries?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="cluster", y="pop", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Cluster")
    ax.set_ylabel("Population")
    ax.set_title("How does population vary across different clusters?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
